Amul R. Thapar has been appointed as a judge on the United States Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit by President Donald J. Trump. Thapar is the first Article III judge of South Asian descent in the country. He previously served on the District Court for the Eastern District of Kentucky and has also held positions as U.S. Attorney for the Eastern District of Kentucky and Assistant U.S. Attorney in the Southern District of Ohio and the District of Columbia. Thapar started his legal career in private practice and has clerked for Judge S. Arthur Spiegel and Judge Nathaniel R. Jones. He received his BS from Boston College and his JD from the University of California, Berkeley.